IMPBPacketType.name: IMPBPacketType
IMPBPacketType.description: Specifies one of 2 Packet Types: 1- IP. 2- ARP. 3- IP+ARP

IMPBLockMode.name: IMPBLockMode
IMPBLockMode.description: Specifies lock/unlock for an entry: 1- Unlocked. 2- Locked.

IMPBDeviceType.name: IMPBDeviceType
IMPBDeviceType.description: Specifies one of 3 Devices Types: 1- HOST. 2- DHCP Server. 3- Router. 4- Router with DHCP.

rlIMPBMngTable.name: rlIMPBMngTable
rlIMPBMngTable.description: The table specifies all IMPB station. The entry contains IP address and MAC of the station and also list of ports, packet type and Device type of this station.

rlIMPBMngEntry.name: rlIMPBMngEntry
rlIMPBMngEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlIMPBMngPortlist.name: rlIMPBMngPortlist
rlIMPBMngPortlist.description: List of ports that the station is configured on.

rlIMPBMngMode.name: rlIMPBMngMode
rlIMPBMngMode.description: Is this station locked or not.

rlIMPBMngRouterBandwidth.name: rlIMPBMngRouterBandwidth
rlIMPBMngRouterBandwidth.description: Specifies, for Router entry, , egress Bandwidth on the associated ports. Zero means disabled.

rlIMPBMngRowStatus.name: rlIMPBMngRowStatus
rlIMPBMngRowStatus.description: A status can be destroy, active or createAndGo

rlIMPBMngAction.name: rlIMPBMngAction
rlIMPBMngAction.description: An action scalar which specifies the global action to take on the management DB.

rlIMPBMngPortBandwidthTable.name: rlIMPBMngPortBandwidthTable
rlIMPBMngPortBandwidthTable.description: The table specifies the Bandwidth value for each Port that at least one Router station is configured on it.

rlIMPBMngPortBandwidthEntry.name: rlIMPBMngPortBandwidthEntry
rlIMPBMngPortBandwidthEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlIMPBMngBandwidth.name: rlIMPBMngBandwidth
rlIMPBMngBandwidth.description: This variable specifies what is the Bandwidth value on the specific ifIndex. Zero means disabled.

rlIMPBMngRouterBandwidthTable.name: rlIMPBMngRouterBandwidthTable
rlIMPBMngRouterBandwidthTable.description: The table shows the Bandwidth information per configured router

rlIMPBMngRouterBandwidthEntry.name: rlIMPBMngRouterBandwidthEntry
rlIMPBMngRouterBandwidthEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlIMPBRouterPortlist.name: rlIMPBRouterPortlist
rlIMPBRouterPortlist.description: List of ports that the router is configured on.

rlIMPBRouterBandwidth.name: rlIMPBRouterBandwidth
rlIMPBRouterBandwidth.description: This variable specifies the Bandwidth value for a specific router, Zero means disabled.

rlIMPBMngDiscoveryLearningStatus.name: rlIMPBMngDiscoveryLearningStatus
rlIMPBMngDiscoveryLearningStatus.description: This variable specifies the discovery is NOW learning or stopped. Setting an entry in rlIMPBMngDiscoverytTable is conditioned with a value of this scalar to be set to noLearning.

rlIMPBMngUncheckPorts.name: rlIMPBMngUncheckPorts
rlIMPBMngUncheckPorts.description: Action scalar that defines which ports the system should be deleted from all entries in the management MIB. If an entry is remained with empty portlist the entry will be deleted also

rlIMPBMngLockedStations.name: rlIMPBMngLockedStations
rlIMPBMngLockedStations.description: Read-only scalar to count how much locked stations there are in the system

rlIMPBMngGratARPPeriodTimeout.name: rlIMPBMngGratARPPeriodTimeout
rlIMPBMngGratARPPeriodTimeout.description: The interval at which ARP Requests are transmitted on behalf of configured stations. The default value for rlIMPBGratARPPeriodTimeout object is Zero, which means don't send ARP Request. The value of this object must be restored from non-volatile storage after a re-initialization of the management system.
